-- EON in Talks With Turkey’s Dogus on Power Investment, HT Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-01-15T09:06:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/eon-is-in-discussions-with-turkey-s-dogus-on-power-investment-ht-reports.html
EON AG (EOAN) ,  Germany ’s biggest utility,
started talks with Dogus Holding AS, a Turkish group with
interests in finance, construction and media, to invest in as
much as 6,000 megawatts of power in Turkey,  Haberturk  reported.  The companies signed a preliminary agreement, the Istanbul-
based newspaper said, without saying where it got the
information. The partnership may also participate in government
sales of  power plants , it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net  